Remove-AzureRmAutoscaleSetting

Removes an Autoscale setting.

Syntax

Remove-AzureRmAutoscaleSetting -ResourceGroup <String> -Name <String> [<CommonParameters>]

Description

The Remove-AzureRmAutoscaleSetting cmdlet removes an Autoscale setting. You must specify the name of the setting and the name of the resource group to which it is assigned.

Examples

1:

Parameters

-ResourceGroup

Specifies the name of the resource group.

Type:String
Required:True
Position:Named
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByPropertyName)
Accept wildcard characters:False
-Name

Specifies the name of the Autoscale setting to remove.

Type:String
Required:True
Position:Named
Default value:None
Accept pipeline input:True (ByPropertyName)
Accept wildcard characters:False

Related Links

  • Add-AzureRmAutoscaleSetting
  • Get-AzureRmAutoscaleSetting
